records.addlTxt:
3:35 PM Defendant Vincent O Gammel in court. Prosecuting attorney Robert A. Gardner in court for the State of Wisconsin. Attorney Rose Yanke in court for State of Wisconsin. 
John Matthews is sworn as a witness and questioned by Attorney Yanke. He is an investigative sergeant with the Wood County Sheriff's Department. Testifies as to his training. On 8/10/22, he conducted a traffic stop due to a moving violation. The driver of the vehicle was the defendant. The witness identifies the defendant in the courtroom.  There were two other people in the vehicle. The canine was brought to the scene and the canine indicated on the vehicle.  Drug paraphernalia was found in the vehicle. The defendant was searched and there was a residue in a cylinder and it tested positive for methamphetamine. A large amount of cash was found on the defendant.  CWD told him that defendant pays him in heroin and he distributes heroin in the community. CWD told him that they stopped at residences on that day to collect money from selling illegal substances. CAP allowed him to  look at her phone and he observed conversations about selling drugs from someone named Frog. He believes the defendant's nickname is Frog. A brown chunky substance that was found in the vehicle tested positive for Fentanyl. The green leafy substance tested positive for THC.  He learned defendant had a pending felony case in Milwaukee.  Defendant was out on bond for that case. Attorney Gardner cross-examines witness.  
Court finds probable cause that a felony was committed and the defendant committed it. Defendant stands mute and Court enters not guilty plea to all counts. Bond is continued.
Final pre-trial scheduled for November 17, 2022 at 03:00 pm.
